Stats SA has released its Living Conditions of Households in South Africa report for 2014/2015, detailing how much South Africans spend on various services. The report on annual household expenditure contains a section on communications, which details how much citizens spend on “postal services, telephone and telefax equipment, and telephone and telefax services”. “On average, South African households spent approximately R3,509 per annum on communication in 2015,” said Stats SA. The table below shows the annual household expenditure on communication by sex, population group of household head, province, and settlement type.